commit.message:
Remove Harmony mode from README, recommend terser

Harmony mode is not up-to-date in UglifyJS, and more likely to cause issues. Recommend ruby-terser as an alternative.
Use built-in Rubocop GitHub Actions formatter

Run tests on GitHub Actions

Travis CI does not offer free minutes for open source projects. GitHub Actions ha sbetter integration with GitHub. Migrating does require dropping Ruby 1.9 and 2.0 from CI matrix, but these have not been maintained for years now.

commit.message:
Defer initialisation of ExecJS context

Wait until context is used before initialising context. This avoids memory leaks with MiniRacer. Fixes #165.

Refactor error context line option handling

Use same terminology in options and code. Drop support for environment variable as that is not available for any other option.
